<paragraph id="8BB136C8FF9AFFF2FF7DFE66FC8AFD6C" blockId="5.[151,1437,254,677]" pageId="5" pageNumber="251">
Remarks: This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D4BFF9AFFF2FD33FE66FC32FDDC" authorityName="Bolanos, Quiroga &amp; Litvaitis" authorityYear="2007" box="[649,936,507,533]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="5" pageNumber="251" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="rawlinsonae">
<emphasis id="B97AEADAFF9AFFF2FD33FE66FC32FDDC" box="[649,936,507,533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="251">Pseudoceros rawlinsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of colours and can only be differentiated on the basis of presence or absence of the marginal band or the colour of the marginal band. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D4BFF9AFFF2FABDFDBDFAE9FDF0" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1901" box="[1287,1395,543,569]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="5" pageNumber="251" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="B97AEADAFF9AFFF2FABDFDBDFAE9FDF0" box="[1287,1395,543,569]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="251">P. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the marginal may be absent, or is yellow to greenish when present while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D4BFF9AFFF2FC04FDD9FBFEFD94" authorityName="Bolanos, Quiroga &amp; Litvaitis" authorityYear="2007" box="[958,1124,579,605]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="5" pageNumber="251" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="rawlinsonae">
<emphasis id="B97AEADAFF9AFFF2FC04FDD9FBFEFD94" box="[958,1124,579,605]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="251">P. rawlinsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is golden yellow to orange. Our specimen shows no golden yellow to orange marginal band, which agrees with one of the morphological variations of 
<emphasis id="B97AEADAFF9AFFF2FF49FD11FEFEFD6C" box="[243,356,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="251">
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D4BFF9AFFF2FF49FD11FEC5FD6C" authorityName="Verrill" authorityYear="1901" box="[243,351,651,677]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="5" pageNumber="251" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="bicolor">P. bicolor</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This is a new record to Indian waters.
</paragraph>
